cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a fast randomized PCA algorithm for dimension reduction and embedding of real data, which is a common task in machine learning. It is also likely to belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the proposed algorithm is tested on large information retrieval data. Additionally, it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the algorithm is optimized for sparse data. It could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as PCA is widely used in social network analysis. Finally, it may belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as PCA is commonly used in image processing and computer vision.
